column1:
Driving on the highway.

My wife: Hey, you just missed a right!

Me: Thanks, babe. You're Mrs. Right!
Jokes about unemployed people aren't funny. They've never worked for me.

A guy got a vasectomy without telling his wife. When she found out, she asked, 'ARE YOU SERIOUS?' angrily.

He replied... 'Yes, I'm not kidding you.'

I went to a pet shop.

I said, 'Can I buy a goldfish?'

The guy said, 'Do you want an aquarium?'

I said, 'I don't care what star sign it is.'
This week's winning lottery numbers are 1, 3, 5, 7, and 9. I mean, what are the odds?
What did the left eye say to the right eye? Between you and me, something smells.

What do you call a deer with no eyes?

No idear...

My friend just rang me and said, 'What are you doing at the moment?'

I said, 'Probably failing my driving test.'

Every machine in the coin factory broke down all of a sudden without explanation.

It just doesn't make any cents.

Why did the scarecrow win an award?

Because he was outstanding in his field!

Why does Trump take anti-anxiety medication?

To prevent Hispanic attacks.
An unraveling string walks into a bar. The bartender asks, 'Are you a string?' The string answers, 'I'm a frayed knot.'

I'm raisin the quality of my puns!

(I've got a grape sense of humor.)

Girlfriend: I'm sick of you pretending you're a detective. I think we should split up.

Me: Good idea - we can cover more ground that way.

I'm really proud of my friend's collection of Hollywood acting equipment.

Props to him.

I could make a million jokes about cash machines...

I just can't think of one atm.

I saw a woman with 12 breasts the other day.

Sounds weird... dozen tit?
All my friends think I'm weird for constantly eating ham and pineapple sandwiches. But hey, that Hawaii roll.
Just learned the word for constipation in German. Farfrompoopen.

Why did the farmer give money to the cow?

So he could have rich milk.
Someone stole $5000 worth of Red Bull from a local delivery truck. How do these people sleep at night!?

What's Batman's favorite fruit?

BA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA

BA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA-NA

Grapefruit.

Never challenge death to a pillow fight.

Unless you're prepared for the reaper cushions.

Why do trees seem suspicious on sunny days?

I don't know, they're just a bit shady.

I saw a slide with an 85 degree incline for sale the other day for $1000.

I thought that's a bit steep!
Iâ€™ve always wanted to be a doctor, but I didnâ€™t have the patience.

How did the sea feel when her boyfriend broke up with her?

EmOCEANal...
My last girlfriend left me for being unnecessarily mysterious... ..or did she?

Why did the terminator kill people even after retirement?

He was an ex-terminator.
I went to the bar with a boxer but he's just a lightweight.

What did the skydiver say when her pack didn't open?

Chute!

COP: Anything in the car I should know about?
ME: Nope, just stuff you shouldn't know about...
COP: Cool. Have a good day!
My wife refuses to go to Karaoke with me. I have to duet alone.

Which celebrity chef would you most like to fix you a meal?
Gordon Ramsay, because he could make even my cooking look good!
It's so cold and windy outside, I just saw a politician with his hands in his own pockets!
Soap is not real food. Even if one digests it, one will have sham poo.

After getting sick of my dad jokes, my wife locked me out of the house.
I texted her: Oh pun the door!

Why was the broken refrigerator so angry?

Because he couldn't keep his cool.
A jumper cable walks into a bar. The bartender says, 'I'll serve you, but don't start anything.'

Why was Santa's little helper depressed?

Because he had low elf esteem.

I saw a dyslexic Yorkshire man the other day.
He was wearing a cat flap.

My wife accused me of being a transvestite.
So I packed up her things and left.

Most people are shocked when they find out...
...how incompetent I am as an electrician.
The local drug dealer started dressing up as a Jehovah's Witness so he wouldn't arouse suspicions. But the police arrested him after they saw people letting him into their homes.

If you're attacked by a mob of clowns...
Go for the juggler.

I just met a brilliant short story writer.
He was 4 foot 1.

Whoever invented the knock-knock joke...
Should get a Nobell prize.
Just lost my job as a zookeeper. In my defense, there were signs everywhere saying please don't feed the animals.
Even when venison is on 2 for 1 - it's still too expensive.

Why can't you explain puns to kleptomaniacs?
They always take things literally.

I used to work at a bar where we had to move the seating to the top of the bar when we closed up.
I had to find other work.
Way too many stool movements for me!

Don't worry if you can't spell big words like 'apocalypse.'
It's not like it's the end of the world.

An Irish priest is driving along a country road when the police pull him over. The officer smells alcohol on the priest's breath.
He asks, 'Have you been drinking?'
'Just water,' says the priest.
The cop replies, 'Then why do I smell wine?'
The priest says, 'Good Lord, He's done it again!'
Please God, let me prove to you that winning the lottery won't change me. :)

Sometimes I like to tuck my knees into my chest and lean forward.
That's just how I roll.

Excuse me, doctorâ€”my husband was rushed in with violent spasms in his buttocks. Where is he, please?'
'ICU, baby, shaking that ass.

I can't believe it's Pancake Tuesday again.
Honestly, it just creped up on me.
I have a urology joke, too, but it would probably piss you off!

Why don't scientists trust atoms?
Because they make up everything! ðŸ˜„

My right arm hurts like crazy, but only between 9 a.m. and 11 a.m.
Worst case of ten-ish elbow ever.
I was in a band during the 80s called The Prevention. We were better than the Cure.

What did the gamer say to their sweetheart?

You had me at Halo!
I'm American and I'm sick of people saying America is the stupidest country in the world. Personally, I think Europe is the stupidest country in the world.

My landlord says he needs to come talk to me about how high my heating bill is.

I told him, my door is always open.

The roundest knight at King Arthur's round table was Sir Cumference, but the one most afraid was Sir Render.
Let's not forget the most resilient, Sir Vival,
And the rotund Sir Cular,
And the knight with the most electrifying personality, Sir Kit!
Wouldn't it have been ironic if everyone went blind in the year 2020?

An ear worm bit my ear today,
And I am quite annoyed.
I cannot shake it from my head,
It is a memoroid.
Today I started an argument with my wife while riding in an elevator. I was wrong on so many levels.
The origami boxing match was showing the other night. Shame though, as it was only on paper-view.
If you cross-breed a caribou and a peacock, do you get a peek-a-boo?
Assuming there is an afterlife, what would you want buried with you so you could use it in the afterlife?
Americans can't switch from pounds to kilograms overnight. That would cause mass confusion.

I looked across the museum hall and spotted my ex-girlfriend, but I just couldn't say hello.

There was just too much history between us.

I asked my wife if she wanted me to pick up Fish and Chips on my way home from work.

I think she regrets allowing me to name our kids.

My girlfriend left me because she couldn't handle my OCD...

I told her to close the door five times on her way out!

Have you heard about the restaurant on the moon?

Great food, but no atmosphere.
According to a recent survey, inserting musical instruments into sentences largely goes unnoticed.
Did you know there's no official training for a garbage collector? They just pick it up as they go.

The Earth teases other planets.

They have no life.

I had a fight with a man on some moving stairs today...

It started at the bottom and just escalated from there.
What do Game of Thrones and The Sixth Sense have in common? Icey dead people.

I'm going to stand outside.

So if anyone asks,

I am outstanding.
What's the difference between a buffalo and a bison? You can't wash your hands in a buffalo!

What's a thousand times better than Instagram?

Instakilogram.
I've washed my hands so many times over these past two years that I found cheat notes from a test I took in 1980...

Why did the jalapeÃ±o break up with the bell pepper?

It couldn't handle the heat!
I asked the checkout girl for a date. She said: They're in the fruit aisle next to the bananas.

I told my doctor I have a problem with my right ear.

He asked if I was sure.

I said: yeah... I'm definite.
My brother always lies. Today he finally admitted to being a pathological liar. Yeah, like I'm falling for that.

Why did the hipster burn his tongue with his pizza?

He ate it before it was cool!
I don't think our kids fully appreciate the fact that we've never killed them. Not even once.

My son: The manual in the car says not to turn up the volume of the stereo to the maximum.

I told him that's... sound advice.
If a restaurant isn't sweet to its chefs, they might dessert.
What's sexually transmitted and has a 100% death rate? Life.

When I turned 18, my dad told me it was time to get a job. When I was your age, my very first job I had I worked with over 500 people under me. Wow, I asked. Did you work in some big corporation? No! He said, I mowed the lawn in a cemetery.

I'm never again donating money to anyone collecting for a marathon.

They just take the money and run!
Money does not buy happiness, but it's better to cry in a sports car than on a bicycle.
Someone just called me emotionless. I don't know how to feel about it.

You call it 'Possession of Marijuana.'

I call it 'Joint Custody.'
Why are pediatricians always so angry? They have very little patients.

A guy cleaning out the closet of his late wife of 50 yrs. He finds a box with 3 eggs, $1K, & a note:

Sorry, I was unfaithful. When I was, I put an egg in the box.

He thought, 50 yrs, 3 eggsâ€”not bad.

He continued to read the note:
Every time I got a dozen eggs, I sold them
The robbers took everything from my house, but I'm most upset they took my mirror. I can't see myself without it.

Why does Santa go down the chimney?

Because Mrs. Claus told him he'd never get in the back door.

Attempted to exercise this morning...
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

didn't work out...
A trucker called me on the CB today and asked what the date was. I said, '10/4, good buddy.'
Did you hear about the cross-eyed teacher? He couldn't control his pupils.

Next Friday my cousin is having a C-section. Her baby will be my first cousin...

Once Removed...

The Energizer Bunny just got arrested.

They charged him with battery.
I once went on a date with a cross-eyed girl. It turns out she was seeing someone else the whole time.

Carpenter ants are just like regular ants

except rainy days and Mondays always get them down...

Where can you get vegan beef?

From a vegetabull.
Scientists concluded that tsunamis occur because the ocean is mad that no one ever waves back.

My wife tried to beat me up with an old Elton John record...

I'm still standing.

Parallel lines have so much in common!

...It's a shame they'll never meet each other.

A policeman stopped me and said he was looking for a man with one eye.

I told him to use both, and he'd find him a lot quicker.
Why do bears have hairy coats? Fur protection.
Learning Norwegian is an Oslo process.

Ordered some Christmas presents online the other day and used my donor card instead of my debit card.

Cost me an arm and a leg.

My wife left me because of my obsession with Linkin Park.

But in the end, it doesn't even matter.

It's important to have a good vocabulary.

If I had known the difference between the words 'antidote' and 'anecdote,'

one of my good friends would still be alive.
I'm annoyed because I had to work at the museum tonight moving suits of armor. I hate knight shifts.
I wasn't originally going to get a brain transplant, but then I changed my mind.
A friend just told me that my daughter and my wife look like twins. I said, 'Well, they were separated at birth.'
I call my kettle Jim Carrey. Because he brews-all-my-tea...
Is a nun having a baby inconceivable?
Every time I make a chicken wrap, I feel so fowl-mouthed.

After my prostate examination, the doctor left, then the nurse came in and whispered three words that no man wants to hear...

'Who was that?'

I challenged the number 1 to a fight, but he brought his friends 3, 5, 7, and 13.

The odds were against me, but I'm primed for it!

What do you call cheese that isn't yours?

Nacho Cheese.

Why don't scientists trust atoms?

Because they make up everything!
A guy on a tractor just drove past me shouting, 'The end of the world is nigh!' It was Farmer Geddon.

Know why a milking stool only has three legs?

Because the cow has the udder.

Why can't you trust the Devil?

Because he's evil with a capital D.

Justice is best served cold.

Because if it were served warm, it would be justwater.

What creature is smarter than a talking parrot?

A spelling bee.

My 6-year-old daughter has lined up all of her dolls towards the outdoor grill.

Looks like she's preparing some kind of barbie queue.
I was in a tornado recently. 'Twas such an awful kind. The wind felt so very strong and totally blew my mind.

I have sex with my wife almost every day!

Almost on Monday, almost on Tuesday, almost on Wednesday...

Guys, when a gal changes in front of you, it means she likes you...

or you've leveled up in the friend zone...

.

.

.

Or she hasn't spotted you in the tree yet...

A guy has just assaulted me with a strawberry-flavored milk!

How dairy!

How do you fit an elephant in a Safeway bag?

You take the s out of safe and the f out of way...

Why don't scientists trust atoms?

Because they make up everything!

I once took the pee out of a pirate.

He was furious!

Acronyms are important, some you should know:
QOTD - Quote of the day
MOTD - Message of the day
TWIT - This week in Trump

Her: Why are the potatoes burnt?

Me: That's for tomorrow.

Her: Huh?

Me: Tomorrow is Black Fry Day.

Why donâ€™t skeletons fight each other?

They donâ€™t have the guts.

What is the best way to observe the two planets between Jupiter and Neptune?

Saturn Uranus.

Anyone remember the 90s, when you'd have to clean your mouse balls?

I'm glad I don't have pets anymore.

I saw a microbiologist today...

They were much bigger than I expected...

An old Texas rancher passed away, leaving his large cattle ranch to his 3 sons.
They decided to rename the ranch and came up with
'Focus'
Because that's where the sons raise meat.
I had a bowling joke, but it struck out.
Why did the belt go to prison? He held up a pair of pants!

I said, 'Alexa, what do women want?'
The darn thing hasn't shut up for the past three days!
Drilling holes is boring.

The inventor of hard-boiled eggs wrapped in sausage meat has just died.
RIP Scott Chegg.

Me: My dog ate my homework...
Professor: Your dog ate your computer program?
Me: It took him a couple of bytes...
In the short time I've been here, I feel like we've all really groan a lot.

I just bought a thesaurus and when I got it home, all the pages were blank.
I have no words to describe how angry I am.

What sound does a cow make when it runs out of milk?
None.
There is udder silence.
Christmas: The time of year when everyone gets Santamental.
I've just deleted all the German names from my phone. Now it's completely Hans-free.

Things that keep me awake at night #498...

Why is there not an all-bacon channel on television?

Harry has decided to go into acting with his wife, Meghan Markle.

He'll be known as the Artist Formerly Known as Prince.

Just bought my wife an artificial leg for Christmas.

It's not her main present, just a stocking filler.
The other day I bought myself a universal remote and thought to myself, well, this changes everything.

At an interview...

First question: Describe yourself in 3 words.

Me: Not very good with numbers.
I went out with a girl whose left breast was made of timber. Just kidding. That would be ridiculous, wooden tit?
My wife and I have an agreement; I don't try to run her life... and I don't try to run mine.

Breaking News:

Federal Authorities rule that you cannot be prescribed medical marijuana if you are taking laxatives.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
Apparently, you need to either shit or get off the pot...
Police arrested two kids, one for eating batteries, the other for eating fireworks. They charged one and let the other one off.

I've just been outside helping a guy in a black robe with a scythe clear the frost off his car.

I was de-icing with death.

I once knew a promiscuous female lawyer who was an ambulance chaser. She was better known as...

run around Sue!

Midwives

Help people out.
I asked a friend how it was going down at the National Ambidextrous Society. He said people are joining left and right.

Today at the bank, an old lady asked me to help check her balance.

So I pushed her over.
eBay is so useless. I tried to look up lighters but all they had was 749 matches.
A man goes to a funeral and asks the widow: Mind if I say a word? She says: Please do. The man clears his throat and says: Bargain. The widow replies: Thanks, that means a great deal.

If I won 298 million, I'd give a quarter of it to charity.

I'm not sure what I'd do with the other $297,999,999.75 though.
A friend of mine tried to annoy me with bird puns, but I soon realized that toucan play at that game.

What do you call a snowman with a six-pack?

An abdominal snowman.

If I'm ever on life support, unplug me...

Then plug me back in, see if that works.

DIET DAY 1

I have removed all the bad food from my home.

It was delicious.
The last time I was someone's type, I was donating blood...

My bank just called me about suspicious activity on my account.

They didn't believe I bought a gym membership.
I started a dating site for chickens. It's not my normal day job. I'm just doing it to make hens meet...
Well, it's 1 for the money, 2 for the show, 3 to get ready... 4 for sales, 5 for customer service, or 6 to hear these options again.
My father doesn't trust anyone. In fact, he has a saying... But he won't tell me.

I asked a guy at the station when the next train was coming.

He said, 'Have a look online!'

I said, 'That's kinda dangerous, isn't it?'

If I had to rate our solar system...

I'd give it one star.

I started out with nothing,
and I still have most of it...

My friend was fired from his lumberjack job after failing to cut down a tree 8 times...
He had exceeded the maximum number of loggin' attempts.

Just bought a suit made from cactus.
I look pretty sharp in it.
My wife tells me I have 2 major faults: I don't listen - and something else.

I'm in a band called Dyslexia.
We've just released our greatest hit album!
Country singers pay for their condoms with their Johnny Cash.
A pirate walks into a bar and it was at that moment that he realized his patch was on the wrong eye.

I would like to be a millionaire just like my dad.
He always wanted to be a millionaire too.

A man walks into a bar with a newt on his shoulder. The bartender says, 'What an interesting pet, what's his name?' 'Tiny,' the man replies. 'What an odd name, why do you call him Tiny?' 'Because... he's my newt.'

Smoking will kill you...
Bacon will kill you...
But...
Smoking bacon will cure it.

My coworker accidentally drank from my Starbucks cup and said, 'Your coffee tastes just like rum.'
.
.
.
Weird, huh...
Where do baby ghosts go during the day? Dayscare!
DON'T SAY MAYBE IF YOU WANT TO SAY NO.
My hair is getting so thin you can see what's on my mind!
I was running around the house naked when I accidentally drank a bottle of Windex (don't ask), but it did stop me from streaking!
My wife just told me that Peter Tork of The Monkees died today. I said, 'No way! Now I'm a bereaver.'
Just a note to the guy who invented zero... thanks for nothing!

I met an English knight yesterday.
Sir William of Purchase
(Bill of Sale to his pals)
If you leave your closet open, your wardrobe might have a coming-out party!
When is a car not a car? When it turns into a driveway.
What's the difference between a bad sharpshooter and a constipated owl? One can shoot but not hit...
A New Year's resolution is something that goes in one year and out the other.
Our janitor just asked if I wanted to smoke some weed with him! I declined... I can't deal with high-maintenance people...
I'm a little confused as to why everyone keeps giving me Legos for my birthday. I don't know what to make of it.
I bought a book called 'How to Scam Idiots on eBay.' That was 3 months ago, and it's still not arrived yet!

What do you call a donkey with 3 legs?

A wonkey.

I needed detergent and a news magazine. I took too long to get to the store, and when I made it, both were sold out.

Time and Tide wait for no man.
I'd just like to thank my English teacher for defining the word 'many' for me. It means a lot.
Went to a zoo that had only one animal - and that was a dog. It was a Shih Tzu.
My fear of stairs is escalating...

Why aren't marijuana dispensaries called

Grass Stations?
As soon as space travel is possible, I'm moving from the Milky Way to the Soy Milky Way galaxy. I'm galactose intolerant.

I didn't want to think my dad was stealing from his construction job...

But when I got home, all the signs were there.

*A calendar was admitted to a hospital.*

Doctor: I'm sorry to say this, but your days are numbered.
Common sense is like deodorant. Those who need it never use it.

What is the difference between an angry circus owner and a Roman barber?

One is a raving showman, the other is a shaving Roman.

Humpty Dumpty had a terrible winter.

Which sucks because he had a great fall.
Have you heard of the new Apple product to protect your eyes? It's called the iLid.
I got a new pair of gloves today, but they're both lefts which, on the one hand, is great, on the other, it's just not right.

I'm writing a song about getting my door lock replaced.

There's a key change at the end.
I'm not particularly bad at cooking, but how long is pasta supposed to stay in the toaster?
I have a library joke; it's really novel!

How do you stop moles from digging up your garden?

Hide their spades.
I taught a creative writing class at a prison. It had its prose and cons.
Is there a best month of spring? There May be.
Siri kept calling me Shirley today. I was starting to get really angry, and then I realized why... I left my phone in Airplane mode.
Why did the iPhone go to the dentist? He had a blue tooth.
What do you say to comfort an English teacher? They're, there, their.

I told my friend I was going to the store to get some duct tape, a shovel, heavy-duty trash bags, and a bottle of bleach. They looked at me and said, 'You know, a simple apology would probably fix things.'

I called my wife and asked her if I should pick up Fish and Chips on the way home from work, and she hung up...

She's still angry she let me name the kids.
I've been prescribed anti-gloating cream. I can't wait to rub it in.

If two wrongs don't make a right, what do two rights make?

An airplane.
I asked my wife for an audiobook this Christmas, but she got me an encyclopedia instead. That speaks volumes.
I hate it when I'm singing to a song on the radio and the artist gets the lyrics wrong!
When you pull a pin from a grenade, how do you put it back in? Quick answers please? (Spoiler: You don't.)

What was a more important invention than the first telephone?
.
.
The second one...

I used to be addicted to candles. I was always buying more than I would ever need.

I managed to taper off.

Why did the scarecrow win an award?

Because he was outstanding in his field!
Sorry for all the animal jokes, but... Alpaca a few more in before I'm done.

I hear it was easy to convince ladies not to eat Tide pods.
But it was harder to deter gents.

Purple is my favorite color!
I like it more than blue and red combined.

Why did the orange stop halfway up the hill?
It ran out of juice.

Why did the Indian chef refuse to work with paper towels?
He said, 'I need pepper and aloo, not paper and a loo!'

What do you call a bunch of rabbits walking backward in a single-file fashion?
A receding hare line.

Wife: Stop being an idiot. Just be yourself.
Me: Make up your mind.

I found a builder who advertises, 'No job too small!'
So I've got him tiling the bathroom in my daughter's dollhouse.

Walking past a farm, I saw a sign that read 'Duck, Eggs.'
I assumed it was an unnecessary comma...
Then it hit me.

What's red and smells?
Rudolph's nose.

What is the medical diagnosis for owning too many dogs?
Roverdose.

My friend is a professional sleepwalker.
He is living the dream.

Having problems trying to organize a hide and seek game.
It's hard to find good players...

If you could have dinner with anyone from history, who would it be?
I'd choose someone who likes to pick up the tab!

God: *Creates worms*
Worm: Thanks for the worm welcome, God!
God: *Creates birds*
Worm: Oh, no...
I wouldn't buy anything with Velcro. It's a total rip-off.

I gave up playing rugby at school.
All the teacher kept saying was nice try.

Someone stole my Michael Jackson albums without me noticing.
What a smooth criminal.

Will glass coffins ever become popular?
Remains to be seen.

Why did the drunkard push his wife off the cliff?
Tequila.
How many zombies would Rob Zombie rob if Rob Zombie could rob zombies?
A soldier who survived mustard gas and pepper spray is now a seasoned veteran.

What do you call a classy fish?

Sofishticated...

Knock Knock

Who's there?

Muffikin

Muffikin who?

Muffikin fingers are trapped in the door.

An oracle once told me it was fate that I had banged my leg into a table at school.

I guess it was my desk to knee.

Son: Hey dad, is that an extinct animal eating lemons?
Dad: Yes son, it's a dino-sour.

My memory is so bad.
How bad is it?
How bad is what?

Why did the chicken cross the playground?
To get to the other slide!

Hey dad, have you seen my sunglasses?
No son, have you seen my dadglasses?

A thief tried to steal the paintings at the Louvre in Paris. He was caught two blocks away when he ran out of gas. He said: I had no Monet to buy Degas to make the Van Gogh. But I tried because I had nothing Toulouse.

Pro Tip:

Save business cards of people you don't like.

If you ever damage a parked car, just write 'sorry' on the back and leave it on the windshield.

People often accuse me of stealing other people's jokes and being a plagiarist.

Their words, not mine.
I have a music joke, but it doesn't sound right.

What kind of music do Elves listen to?

Wrap music.
Why do 9 ants get to live in an apartment for free? Because they're not tenants.
A warning to the person who stole my glasses. I have contacts!

You can't run through a campsite.

You can only ran, because it's past tents.
Lent is Fast Approaching

My recliner and I...

We go way back...

Man arrested after falling into farm machinery while trying to steal it.

He is due to be bailed next Friday!
It's a safe bet that the person who put the first 'r' in February also decided how to spell Wednesday.
Somebody stole the gear stick from my car. Obviously, some shiftless thief...
You know you're ugly when a boiling kettle won't even give you a whistle.
Remember if you lose a sock in the dryer, it comes back as a Tupperware lid that doesn't fit anything.
What's something that never gets old? A classic joke book.
I was driving my date to her house and told her that I wasn't good with directions; she just laughed at me... So, I left her right there.
I've lost 20% of my sight. Sigh...

What do you call a floating dog?

A good buoy!
What did the scarf say to the hat? I'll hang around here. You go on ahead.
It seems my doctor has a crush on me and she really likes my fashion sense. She told me that I have serious healthy shoes.

Last night I ate a piece of string.

I kid you knot.

Can you give someone a skin graft from your butt?

Asking for a friend.

What did the scientist tell his sister when she wouldn't sit still?

Stasis.

Who is carpe?

Why does he DM everyone?
Someone dropped a power tool on my head the other day. One minute I was fine, then BOSCH!
If Watson isn't the most famous doctor in the world... Then Who is.

I saw my dog walk over sandpaper...

All he had to say was 'Rough, rough!'
And the Lord said unto John, 'Come forth and you will receive eternal life.' John came fifth and won a toaster.
